subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis
. Body length, female, 
28.74 mm
(27.62–30.60; n=5), male, 
29.43 mm
(28.45–30.97; n=5). Female: Head with elevated prominences adjacent to ocelli with appearance of horns (
Fig. 1
); middle ocellus clearly below level of lateral ocelli and upper margin of eyes; area between parapsidal line and mesoscutal disc with sparse punctation (punctures separated by three or more puncture diameters); wings brown to dark brown with blue-violet iridescence (
Fig. 3
); pubescence evenly black; integument of terga evenly black; T1 to T4 with scattered minute punctures; T2 to T4 with minute hairs, T5 hairs 0.49–1.02 (length respect MOD). Male: Terga yellowish-orange, with no bands (
Fig. 10
); metasoma with yellowish orange pubescence; posterior tibia internal distal extreme with a notable sharp projection but with apex rounded, anterior margin with a rounded prominence, width of projection two thirds the width of the tibia (
Fig. 9
); length of hairs on terga respect MOD, T2 0.71–1.59, T3 0.77–1.28, T4 0.79–1.42, T5 0.81–1.54; tip of the lateral process of the gonostylus ending broad, rhomboid shaped (
Fig. 103
).

Distribution ( Fig. 132 ). Present in Barbados , Brazil , Colombia , Costa Rica , Ecuador , El Salvador , French Guiana, Guadalupe, Guatemala , Guyana , Honduras , Martinique, Mexico , Nicaragua , Panama , Saint Kitts and Nevis Islands, Trinidad and Tobago , and Venezuela ( Gonzalez & Gonzalez 2009 ; Moure 2012 ; Mawdsley 2018 ). It has also been reported for Bolivia and Peru by Moure (2012) , however according to Hurd (1978) the presence of this species in those countries is seemingly an error, and none of the supporting references giving distributional records in Moure’s compilation are posterior to Hurd’s assertion. Widely distributed in Mexico and Central America, in the ecoregions (
Dinerstein et al . 2017
): Dry forests of Balsas, Dry forests of Central America, Pine-oak forests of Central America, Dry forests of the Central Depression of Chiapas , Seasonal humid forests of Costa Rica , Humid isthmus-Atlantic forests, Humid isthmus-Pacific forests, Dry forests of Jalisco, Mesoamerican mangroves of the Gulf and Caribbean, Mangrove of the Mesoamerican Pacific north, Dry forest of Panama , Humid forests of PetenVeracruz, Sierra of the Tuxtlas-Veracruz, Humid forests of the Sierra Madre of Chiapas, Pine-oak forests of the Sierra Madre of Oaxaca, Pine-oak forests of the Sierra Madre del Sur, Pine-oak forests of the Sierra Madre Occidental, Dry forests of Sinaloa, Mangroves of the South Pacific of Mesoamerica, Dry forests of the South Pacific, Mountainous forests of Talamanca, Pine-oak forests of the Trans-Mexican Volcanic Belt, Dry forests of Veracruz, and Humid forests of Veracruz. Broad altitudinal distribution, 0 to 2620 m .
